00:10:24.260 --> 00:10:26.600
- Whoa, we'll miss the start of the movie.

263
00:10:26.600 --> 00:10:32.260
- Have fun.

264
00:10:32.260 --> 00:10:34.700
- Thanks, Jewel, I'll call you as soon as we're done

265
00:10:34.700 --> 00:10:36.240
and tell you all about it.

266
00:10:36.240 --> 00:10:37.800
- Great, I can't wait.

267
00:10:38.800 --> 00:10:41.880
(Marinette giggling)

268
00:10:41.880 --> 00:10:50.180
- You can't let Rose and Prem be alone together.

269
00:10:50.180 --> 00:10:51.760
Come on, get up.

270
00:10:51.760 --> 00:10:53.660
We're going to the movie so you can tell them

271
00:10:53.660 --> 00:10:55.020
how you really feel.

272
00:10:55.020 --> 00:10:56.160
Be a fighter.

273
00:10:56.160 --> 00:11:02.500
- Hey, Julica.

274
00:11:02.500 --> 00:11:06.260
What's wrong, sis?

275
00:11:06.260 --> 00:11:07.760
- Why aren't you here anymore?

276
00:11:07.760 --> 00:11:09.340
- Of course I'm here, see?

277
00:11:09.340 --> 00:11:12.140
- No, you're no longer here beside me.

278
00:11:12.140 --> 00:11:13.940
Now that there's an ocean between us,

279
00:11:13.940 --> 00:11:15.580
nothing's the same anymore.

280
00:11:15.580 --> 00:11:17.520
We used to be able to tell each other everything

281
00:11:17.520 --> 00:11:19.180
all the time, now I'm all alone.

282
00:11:19.180 --> 00:11:20.480
- You have Rose.

283
00:11:20.480 --> 00:11:24.020
- What if she left me someday like you did?

284
00:11:24.020 --> 00:11:25.780
What if she found someone better than me?

285
00:11:25.780 --> 00:11:27.080
Someone who's like her,

286
00:11:27.080 --> 00:11:29.460
someone she can share everything with?

287
00:11:29.460 --> 00:11:31.260
- Stop it, Jewel, I'm sure you're getting worried

288
00:11:31.260 --> 00:11:32.100
over nothing.

289
00:11:32.100 --> 00:11:35.100
- You don't know that, you're not here.

290
00:11:35.100 --> 00:11:37.960
There's only one person I can count on anyway, myself.

291
00:11:37.960 --> 00:11:48.880
- Yeah, things are always better with action.

292
00:11:48.880 --> 00:11:56.720
- No need to grab my shoulders during the movie, okay?

293
00:11:56.720 --> 00:11:58.020
It's not going to scare me.

294
00:12:04.020 --> 00:12:06.000
- If you fold it along z-dotted lines,

295
00:12:06.000 --> 00:12:07.300
you get a paper bath.

296
00:12:07.300 --> 00:12:10.140
- Then you can throw it at the right time during the movie.

297
00:12:10.140 --> 00:12:18.580
- Shoot, sorry, I'm sorry.

298
00:12:18.580 --> 00:12:19.980
I forgot to turn it off.

299
00:12:19.980 --> 00:12:24.480
- Luca?

300
00:12:24.480 --> 00:12:25.640
- Did something happen between you and Julica?

301
00:12:25.640 --> 00:12:27.620
- No, things are good, why?

302
00:12:34.920 --> 00:12:36.620
- Horrific evening, everyone.

303
00:12:36.620 --> 00:12:38.400
And welcome to this special screening

304
00:12:38.400 --> 00:12:40.700
of the vampire horrific musical show.

305
00:12:40.700 --> 00:12:42.960
For the first time in France,

306
00:12:42.960 --> 00:12:45.660
you're about to watch an extended, unreleased version

307
00:12:45.660 --> 00:12:48.840
with exclusive and even more terrifying footage.

308
00:12:48.840 --> 00:12:51.600
30 additional minutes of thrill, anguish,

309
00:12:51.600 --> 00:12:54.380
horror, terror, fear, freight.

310
00:12:54.380 --> 00:12:56.340
- I would have been fine stopping at anguish.

311
00:12:56.340 --> 00:12:57.940
- You can leave if you want to, Marinette.

312
00:12:57.940 --> 00:12:59.740
- Oh, no nonsense, I love it when my heart

313
00:12:59.740 --> 00:13:00.820
jumps out of my chest.

314
00:13:00.820 --> 00:13:02.480
Horror movies are the best.

315
00:13:02.480 --> 00:13:04.120
Horror movies are the best.

316
00:13:04.120 --> 00:13:07.180
- Where are you going, Princess Rose?

317
00:13:07.180 --> 00:13:09.720
- Julica's not okay, and it's my fault.

318
00:13:09.720 --> 00:13:12.620
She's always there for me, and tonight I'm not there for her.

319
00:13:12.620 --> 00:13:14.000
I didn't realize she'd be so sad

320
00:13:14.000 --> 00:13:15.800
if I went to this movie without her.

321
00:13:15.800 --> 00:13:19.000
- I'll go with Rose.

322
00:13:19.000 --> 00:13:20.400
- No, you stay, I'll go.

323
00:13:20.400 --> 00:13:21.800
- No, no, no, this is an important moment

324
00:13:21.800 --> 00:13:22.840
for you and your grandparents.

325
00:13:22.840 --> 00:13:24.000
- You're gonna miss the movie.

326
00:13:24.000 --> 00:13:25.740
- It's okay, I already hate it anyway.

327
00:13:25.740 --> 00:13:26.580
- But--

328
00:13:26.580 --> 00:13:28.000
- Adrian, you were right all along.

329
00:13:28.000 --> 00:13:30.040
I still don't like horror movies,

330
00:13:30.040 --> 00:13:31.420
but I was afraid not coming with you

331
00:13:31.420 --> 00:13:33.080
would drive us away from each other,

332
00:13:33.080 --> 00:13:34.440
that you'd be disappointed in me,

333
00:13:34.440 --> 00:13:36.120
that you'd love me less.

334
00:13:36.120 --> 00:13:38.160
- Marinette, the only thing that could disappoint me

335
00:13:38.160 --> 00:13:39.920
is if you feel you can't be honest with me

336
00:13:39.920 --> 00:13:41.320
and you force yourself to do something

337
00:13:41.320 --> 00:13:43.120
you don't want to just to please me.

338
00:13:43.120 --> 00:13:48.020
- The blame falls upon me.

339
00:13:48.020 --> 00:13:49.460
I'm the one who caused such distress

340
00:13:49.460 --> 00:13:50.600
between Rose and Julica.

341
00:13:50.600 --> 00:13:52.500
I need something horrific.

342
00:13:52.500 --> 00:13:54.740
I'm horrific, I'm horrific.

343
00:14:02.280 --> 00:14:04.280
(gasps)

344
00:14:04.280 --> 00:14:07.820
- Hello, forgive my intrusion,

345
00:14:07.820 --> 00:14:10.060
but I sensed a great deal of guilt.

346
00:14:10.060 --> 00:14:11.820
- Get out of my head, evil supervillain.

347
00:14:11.820 --> 00:14:13.560
I've done enough harm as it is today.

348
00:14:13.560 --> 00:14:16.120
If I listen to you, I'll make someone else brokenhearted.

349
00:14:16.120 --> 00:14:18.320
- You're wrong about my intentions, dear Prem.

350
00:14:18.320 --> 00:14:21.700
People think I'm an evil person, like the former Hawk Moth,

351
00:14:21.700 --> 00:14:24.800
when really, I only want to help my fellow humans.

352
00:14:24.800 --> 00:14:26.000
- Why should I believe you?

353
00:14:26.000 --> 00:14:29.000
- Because I'm offering you the power of your choosing

354
00:14:29.000 --> 00:14:32.200
and I'm not asking for anything in return.

355
00:14:32.200 --> 00:14:35.480
Not even Ladybug and Cat Noir's miraculous.

356
00:14:35.480 --> 00:14:38.840
What more do you need to believe I'm acting selflessly?

357
00:14:38.840 --> 00:14:40.180
- You're not tricking me?

358
00:14:40.180 --> 00:14:41.360
- Of course not.

359
00:14:41.360 --> 00:14:44.120
Just tell me what I should call you and see for yourself.

360
00:14:44.120 --> 00:14:45.660
- Fine.

361
00:14:45.660 --> 00:14:47.760
Then call me Count Vampigami.

362
00:14:47.760 --> 00:14:56.340
(upbeat music)

363
00:14:59.940 --> 00:15:02.580
- If Princess Rose and Julica can't come to the movie,

364
00:15:02.580 --> 00:15:04.940
the movie will come to the princesses.

365
00:15:04.940 --> 00:15:10.020
- Go, I think we should get out of here.

366
00:15:10.020 --> 00:15:16.180
- I'm not Prem, I'm Count Vampigami.

367
00:15:29.900 --> 00:15:31.900
- What's happening?

368
00:15:31.900 --> 00:15:33.400
- Come on, Hunter.

369
00:15:33.400 --> 00:15:41.940
- Be quiet, Marinette.

370
00:15:41.940 --> 00:15:44.920
Don't say a word and whatever you do, do not transform.

371
00:15:44.920 --> 00:15:47.220
There's a video camera above.

372
00:15:47.220 --> 00:15:49.520
Unlike Kwamis, you can be filmed and recorded,

373
00:15:49.520 --> 00:15:51.860
so just act like you're afraid of the akumatized villain

374
00:15:51.860 --> 00:15:53.260
and you've come here to hide.

375
00:15:57.360 --> 00:16:00.100
(dramatic music)

376
00:16:00.100 --> 00:16:11.140
- Plagg, claws out.

377
00:16:11.140 --> 00:16:15.920
- Trataclystal.

378
00:16:15.920 --> 00:16:21.960
- Princess Rose, stay, stay.

379
00:16:21.960 --> 00:16:24.920
Vampigami and his friends will go get Julica for you.

380
00:16:24.920 --> 00:16:27.160
- If leading that girl alone is beyond your skills,

381
00:16:27.160 --> 00:16:29.920
then you're the worst vampire friend there is.

382
00:16:29.920 --> 00:16:32.660
- I'm not in the mood for jokes, fuzzbucket.

383
00:16:32.660 --> 00:16:35.540
Step aside or get ready to express regret.

384
00:16:35.540 --> 00:16:43.600
- Okay, so I guess we won't be premiering

385
00:16:43.600 --> 00:16:45.040
our duet and concert.

386
00:16:45.040 --> 00:16:45.880
- Too bad.

387
00:16:45.880 --> 00:16:54.120
- Cataclysm, cataclysm, cataclysm.

388
00:16:54.120 --> 00:16:56.560
Cataclysm.

389
00:16:57.960 --> 00:16:59.320
(panting)

390
00:16:59.320 --> 00:17:01.200
- A super ladybug would give me wings,

391
00:17:01.200 --> 00:17:03.160
provided that her phone rings.

392
00:17:03.160 --> 00:17:15.740
- Locked doors at the theater, a camera in the bathroom,

393
00:17:15.740 --> 00:17:17.040
it's like someone knew that there'd be

394
00:17:17.040 --> 00:17:18.400
an akumatization there today.

395
00:17:18.400 --> 00:17:19.940
- It could be a trap from the new holder,

396
00:17:19.940 --> 00:17:21.380
the Butterfly Miraculous.

397
00:17:21.380 --> 00:17:23.820
- I don't know, but we're gonna have to be extra careful.

398
00:17:23.820 --> 00:17:25.180
Tiki, spots on.

399
00:17:27.780 --> 00:17:29.880
(beeping)

400
00:17:29.880 --> 00:17:30.720
- Got your message.

401
00:17:30.720 --> 00:17:31.720
On my way, kitty cat.

402
00:17:31.720 --> 00:17:38.960
- Why prevent love from prevailing?

403
00:17:38.960 --> 00:17:42.300
Join the ranks, Cat Noir, or the ranks will join you.

404
00:17:42.300 --> 00:17:49.040
- For now, I'll be the one joining him.

405
00:17:49.040 --> 00:17:50.600
Keep away from the kitty vampire.

406
00:17:50.600 --> 00:17:52.740
- Oh, my lady, so glad to see you.

407
00:17:52.740 --> 00:17:56.880
- Yeah, same, I'm super glad I love scary vampires.

408
00:17:57.780 --> 00:18:00.020
(grunting)

409
00:18:00.020 --> 00:18:05.660
- And these ones sing, too.

410
00:18:05.660 --> 00:18:08.360
Bappa got me over there, she's the one running the show.

411
00:18:08.360 --> 00:18:10.260
- Does it look terrifying at all?

412
00:18:10.260 --> 00:18:12.060
(laughing)

413
00:18:12.060 --> 00:18:13.460
- Is that noise coming from you?

414
00:18:13.460 --> 00:18:14.460
- No, what noise?

415
00:18:14.460 --> 00:18:16.360
Oh, right, it's my fingers, I can't help it.

416
00:18:16.360 --> 00:18:18.800
Whenever I hear music, I have to snap my fingers.

417
00:18:18.800 --> 00:18:21.040
(laughing)

418
00:18:28.020 --> 00:18:31.880
- This music does make you wanna sing and clap your hands.

419
00:18:31.880 --> 00:18:33.080
- Bappa got me, on the other hand,

420
00:18:33.080 --> 00:18:34.560
must be stopped for clapping his hands.

421
00:18:34.560 --> 00:18:36.860
- Well spotted, lady, when he claps his hands,

422
00:18:36.860 --> 00:18:39.160
his soma dancers get new bat origamis.

423
00:18:39.160 --> 00:18:40.000
- Hi, friend.

424
00:18:40.000 --> 00:18:41.220
- Pigelle, purple tigress,

425
00:18:41.220 --> 00:18:43.460
you're right on time for the vampire dance.

426
00:18:43.460 --> 00:18:46.800
- Cat Noir, get the party started with your cataclysms.

427
00:18:46.800 --> 00:18:48.800
I've got you covered, let's do charm!

428
00:18:48.800 --> 00:18:55.980
- Cataclysm!

429
00:18:55.980 --> 00:18:58.480
Superheroes always make the best games,

430
00:18:58.480 --> 00:19:01.920
so you zombies can put away your things.

431
00:19:01.920 --> 00:19:04.360
- Purple tigress, you're up.

432
00:19:04.360 --> 00:19:05.620
- Gladly.

433
00:19:05.620 --> 00:19:06.460
- Clout!

434
00:19:06.460 --> 00:19:07.300
- Out!

435
00:19:07.300 --> 00:19:15.860
- Pigelle, you're next!

436
00:19:15.860 --> 00:19:16.700
Get!

437
00:19:25.980 --> 00:19:28.720
(dramatic music)

438
00:19:28.720 --> 00:19:37.660
- No more evil doing for you, Ultracouma.

439
00:19:37.660 --> 00:19:43.460
Time to de-evilize!

440
00:19:43.460 --> 00:19:48.360
Gotcha!

441
00:19:48.360 --> 00:19:51.100
I buy a little butterfly.

442
00:19:51.100 --> 00:19:54.340
Miraculous ladybug!

443
00:19:55.980 --> 00:19:58.740
(dramatic music)

444
00:19:58.740 --> 00:20:05.560
- Ladybug, what did I do?

445
00:20:05.560 --> 00:20:13.160
- This magical charm will help you remember

446
00:20:13.160 --> 00:20:14.660
that you can dance on your own,

447
00:20:14.660 --> 00:20:17.000
or with another person, or even in a group,

448
00:20:17.000 --> 00:20:19.400
but that some people may just not wanna dance,

449
00:20:19.400 --> 00:20:21.100
and that's okay too.

450
00:20:21.100 --> 00:20:21.940
- Pounded!

451
00:20:26.980 --> 00:20:29.080
- Cat Noir, the new holder of the Miraculous

452
00:20:29.080 --> 00:20:30.340
is not trying to defeat us

453
00:20:30.340 --> 00:20:32.340
by using their akumatized villains to fight us.

454
00:20:32.340 --> 00:20:35.580
They wanna defeat us by figuring out who we really are.

455
00:20:35.580 --> 00:20:36.720
They're spying on us.

456
00:20:36.720 --> 00:20:39.020
I already had a feeling, but it was confirmed today.

457
00:20:39.020 --> 00:20:40.720
We've gotta stay alert.

458
00:20:40.720 --> 00:20:42.060
- You can count on me.

459
00:20:42.060 --> 00:20:45.120
I'm sorry, Princess Julica.

460
00:20:45.120 --> 00:20:46.660
I never wanted to form rain clouds

461
00:20:46.660 --> 00:20:49.060
in the blue sky of your relationship with Princess Rose,

462
00:20:49.060 --> 00:20:50.060
or upset you.

463
00:20:50.060 --> 00:20:51.360
If this is going to bring you sadness,

464
00:20:51.360 --> 00:20:53.540
I'd rather not see the movie with Princess Rose.

465
00:20:53.540 --> 00:20:54.640
You go with her.

466
00:20:56.980 --> 00:20:58.500
- I'm not upset with you, Prem.

467
00:20:58.500 --> 00:20:59.940
I'm upset with myself,

468
00:20:59.940 --> 00:21:02.440
because I felt like since you and Rose liked the same movie,

469
00:21:02.440 --> 00:21:04.940
you were meant for each other more than Rose and me.

470
00:21:04.940 --> 00:21:06.040
- No way, Jul.

471
00:21:06.040 --> 00:21:08.340
It's nothing like that.

472
00:21:08.340 --> 00:21:10.920
- I'm so scared of losing you,

473
00:21:10.920 --> 00:21:13.620
but I'm gonna try to overcome that fear.

474
00:21:13.620 --> 00:21:15.660
- Just because we don't do everything together

475
00:21:15.660 --> 00:21:18.300
doesn't mean that we don't love each other very much,

476
00:21:18.300 --> 00:21:21.020
and there's no one I love more than you, Jul.

477
00:21:21.020 --> 00:21:24.840
- Go see the movie together.

478
00:21:24.840 --> 00:21:25.660
I'll be fine.

479
00:21:25.660 --> 00:21:26.960
- Or you go.

480
00:21:26.960 --> 00:21:28.800
You can have my ticket if you want.

481
00:21:28.800 --> 00:21:29.640
- Have mine.

482
00:21:29.640 --> 00:21:31.140
I hate horror movies anyway.

483
00:21:31.140 --> 00:21:32.100
- Are you sure?

484
00:21:32.100 --> 00:21:34.180
- Rose is right.

485
00:21:34.180 --> 00:21:35.780
Just because you don't do everything together

486
00:21:35.780 --> 00:21:37.720
doesn't mean that you love each other less.

487
00:21:37.720 --> 00:21:39.680
- Hey kids, time to go.

488
00:21:39.680 --> 00:21:42.180
- Oh, we'll miss this start of the movie.

489
00:21:42.180 --> 00:21:45.420
- I love you. - I love you.

490
00:21:45.420 --> 00:21:46.660
- Gag me.

491
00:21:46.660 --> 00:21:49.860
More couples just means more fun breaking them up.

492
00:21:56.660 --> 00:21:59.340
(Rose squealing)

493
00:21:59.340 --> 00:22:18.680
- It has to be her.

494
00:22:18.680 --> 00:22:20.820
It's the only logical explanation.

495
00:22:20.820 --> 00:22:22.360
- If it were her, she would have transformed

496
00:22:22.360 --> 00:22:24.120
right there and then, but she didn't.

497
00:22:24.120 --> 00:22:25.620
- I'm missing something.

498
00:22:25.620 --> 00:22:26.540
- It's not possible.

499
00:22:26.540 --> 00:22:27.900
It has to be her.

500
00:22:27.900 --> 00:22:30.040
- You have to explore other avenues, Lila.

501
00:22:30.040 --> 00:22:34.400
- Tatsu, drive me home.
